==Old English==

===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*swefno-'', from Indo-European ''*su̯epno-'', an extension of ''*su̯ep-'' ‘sleep’.

Cognate with Old Saxon ''sweƀan'', Old Norse [[svefn]] (Norwegian [[svevn]]); the IE root also led to Greek [[ὕπνος]], Latin [[somnus]], Old Irish [[suan]], Old Church Slavonic [[съпати]] (Russian [[спать]]), Latvian [[sapnis]], .

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /swevn̩/

===Noun===
'''swefn''' ''n'' (''pl'' '''swefnu''')
# a [[dream]]

===Descendents===
English [[sweven]].

